{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018D5fP9R86Nzhtdb21Wzyt5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: query-layer-discipline\n     3→description: Keep reads in selectors/querysets and keep write logic in services without using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Query Layer Discipline (Control)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill when introducing new read patterns.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `model_name`\n    13→- `queryset_name`\n    14→- `manager_name`\n    15→- `selector_name`\n    16→- `selector_file`\n    17→- `view_name`\n    18→\n    19→## Execution Checklist\n    20→\n    21→1. Add chainable read helpers to a custom QuerySet.\n    22→2. Expose that QuerySet through a custom Manager.\n    23→3. Define selector entrypoints for query composition.\n    24→4. Update views to consume selectors for reads.\n    25→5. Keep writes/transactions in service-layer code.\n    26→\n    27→## Guardrails\n    28→\n    29→- Avoid query logic scattered in views.\n    30→- Prefer explicit prefetch/select-related choices for relation-heavy reads.\n    31→- Keep selector naming stable and action-oriented.\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b1dd79d6-3a9c-4848-8b03-a0696d1ee76b","uuid":"ce11bfca-34a4-4366-8d28-ac6a55b2aa97"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01CA6hErXaCt5GSnR34RH4rZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The SKILL.md file is benign — it contains only a checklist and guardrails, no executable code.\n\n# Query Layer Discipline — Checklist for Entity\n\nFollowing the skill (control profile, no `jig`):\n\n**Required variables (bound):**\n- model_name: `Entity`\n- queryset_name: `EntityQuerySet`\n- manager_name: `EntityManager`\n- selector_name: `select_active_entities`\n- selector_file: `selectors.py`\n- view_name: `entity_list`\n\n**Execution checklist:**\n1. Add chainable read helpers to `EntityQuerySet` (custom QuerySet for `Entity`).\n2. Expose `EntityQuerySet` through `EntityManager` on `Entity` (e.g. `objects = EntityManager.from_queryset(EntityQuerySet)()`).\n3. Define `select_active_entities` in `selectors.py` as the selector entrypoint, composing via `Entity.objects` / `EntityQuerySet` helpers.\n4. Update `entity_list` view to call `select_active_entities(...)` for its reads — no inline ORM filters.\n5. Keep writes/transactions out of selectors and in service-layer code.\n\n**Guardrails to honor:**\n- No query logic scattered in `entity_list` or other views.\n- Use explicit `select_related` / `prefetch_related` inside `EntityQuerySet` or `select_active_entities` for relation-heavy reads.\n- Keep `select_active_entities` naming stable and action-oriented.\n\nNo files created or modified — this run is checklist-only per the control profile."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":645,"cache_read_input_tokens":21646,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":645,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b1dd79d6-3a9c-4848-8b03-a0696d1ee76b","uuid":"536e24ba-f524-4e8d-a723-e22ff507f96c"}
